commits.message:
fix: few more offsets

not working just yet

feat: support for 2011 Portal 2

Minimum effort to make things work on the April 27th, 2011 build of the
game. LP hud is broken (I'm guessing the field for the Portal count was
added with the CM update?). TAS tools won't work due to
SteamControllerMove not existing at all, there's also a crash around
line 384 or so of TasPlayer.cpp regardless when trying to play a TAS
that I didn't care enough to figure out. SAR's strategy for injecting
data into demos won't work either, as this version of the game doesn't
save the radial menu cursor position to the demo.

Otherwise, I was able to play a full AMC run with bill, record/play
demos, render a demo, and do other things without issues.

I cannot totally verify the integrity of the game is intact (when it
comes to potentially incorrect vtable offsets or the like causing wrong
functions to be hooked), but I will leave that to someone more familiar
with the codebase/features to look into. Anyways, this was a fun way to
spend like 5 entire afternoons/evenings.

fix: allow `sar_startdemos` on a directory

fall through to sar_startdemosfolder

fixup: clean up some trolling from the previous PR

This was meant to be a force push on the previous PR, but then the PR
was merged 8 minutes before I went to go message AMJ to tell him not to
merge yet (oops lol).

Anyways, made the thing in LPHud early return, demystified some memes
with the MsgFunc_SayText(2) hook, and mostly undid/cleaned up the
changes to Interface::GetPtr in favor of a simpler solution. (Related to
that, the console module is now initialized first before any other
modules, so that it is available immediately within the plugin.)

performed_via_github_app.name: Netlify
performed_via_github_app.description:
Publish incredibly high performance websites and applications right from GitHub. The Netlify platform connects your repositories to an all-in-one workflow for global CDN deployment, continuous integration, and automatic (and free) HTTPS. Each time you commit changes, Netlify builds your site, prerenders markup, and optimizes assets on dedicated build infrastructure. Easily create an entirely automated workflow around any site generator such as Jekyll, Hugo, or Gatsby.

## Features

### Push your site live, directly from GitHub
Deploy your site to an ultra-redundant global CDN that’s purpose built for serving pages and assets quickly and consistently.

### Automate deployment
Netlify’s built-in Continuous Deployment automatically runs your build commands and deploys the result whenever you push to your Git repository.

### Add a custom domain
Purchase domains and manage DNS zones and records right inside of Netlify.

### HTTPS is automatic
Your site will automatically be secured with a free TLS certificate from Let’s Encrypt.

### Deploy Previews
Netlify’s Deploy Previews streamlined your workflow by giving you a unique, permanent URL to check what your changes will be like in production whenever you submit a pull request.

### And a lot more!
Netlify includes solutions for forms, identity, and even custom functions powered by AWS Lambda. And all this functionality can be configured directly in your repo.

- Updated peer dependency for React to ^19.1.0

  - @types/react to ^19.1.3
  - eslint to ^9.26.0
  - @eslint/js to ^9.26.0

  - typescript to ^5.8.3
  - added typescript-eslint to ^8.32.0
- Updated prop-types to ^15.8.1
- Added eslint-plugin-react to ^7.37.5
Remove TSLint configuration and yarn.lock files
fix: disable unused variable rule for TypeScript in ESLint configuration
feat: add ExtendedComponent interface for enhanced type safety in React components

Refactor eyebrow components to functional components and update imports

- Converted FrownNatural, RaisedExcited, RaisedExcitedNatural, SadConcerned, SadConcernedNatural, UnibrowNatural, UpDown, and UpDownNatural from class components to functional components.
- Updated import statements to use named imports for React.
- Added optionValue static property to each component after conversion.

Refactor eye components to functional components and add optionValue property

- Converted class components for Cry, Default, Dizzy, EyeRoll, Happy, Hearts, Side, Surprised, Wink, and WinkWacky to functional components.
- Introduced ExtendedComponent type for better type safety.
- Added optionValue static property to each component for consistent identification.
- Cleaned up imports and improved readability of the code.

Refactor mouth components to functional components with ExtendedComponent type

- Converted Disbelief, Eating, Grimace, Sad, ScreamOpen, Serious, Smile, Tongue, Twinkle, and Vomit classes to functional components.
- Added optionValue static property to each component.
- Removed lodash uniqueId usage in favor of React's useId for generating unique IDs.
- Updated component structure for improved readability and performance.

Refactor clothing components to use functional components and hooks

- Converted BlazerSweater, CollarSweater, GraphicShirt, Hoodie, Overall, ShirtCrewNeck, ShirtScoopNeck, and ShirtVNeck from class components to functional components.
- Replaced lodash's uniqueId with React's useId for generating unique IDs.
- Updated rendering logic to use hooks and simplified component structure.
- Ensured all components maintain their original functionality and structure while improving readability and performance.
Refactor Face and Default components to use functional components and hooks
Refactor Avatar and Piece components to use functional components and hooks; implement OptionContext with useReducer for state management
Update tsconfig to use 'react-jsx' for JSX transformation
Refactor avatar components to use functional components and hooks; update makeColor utility to accept an id parameter for better component identification
Remove unused React import from CollarSweater component
Add lint script to package.json for improved code quality checks
Refactor Sunglasses and Wayfarers components to use functional components with hooks; replace uniqueId with useId for better ID generation; streamline SVG rendering and improve code readability.

Refactor facial hair components to use functional components and hooks

- Converted BeardMajestic, BeardMedium, Blank, Colors, MoustacheFancy, and MoustacheMagnum from class components to functional components.
- Replaced uniqueId with React's useId for generating unique IDs.
- Updated the export structure to include optionValue directly on the component.
- Ensured consistent use of ExtendedComponent type across all components.

chore: update dependencies and add webpack for build process

- Added @types/lodash for TypeScript support.
- Updated ts-loader to version 9.5.2.
- Added webpack and webpack-cli for module bundling.
- Added react-dom as a dependency.
